Analysts See $0.14 EPS for Calgon Carbon (CCC); Meritor Has 1.33 Sentiment


					
						July 26, 2017 - By Winifred Garcia


Meritor, Inc. is a supplier of a range of integrated systems, modules and components to original equipment manufacturers and the aftermarket for the commercial vehicle, transportation and industrial sectors. The company has market cap of $1.60 billion. The Company’s divisions include Commercial Truck & Industrial and Aftermarket & Trailer. It has a 2.89 P/E ratio. The Commercial Truck & Industrial segment supplies drivetrain systems and components, including axles, drivelines and braking and suspension systems, for medium- and heavy-duty trucks, off-highway, military, construction, bus and coach, fire and emergency and other applications in North America, South America, Europe and Asia Pacific.







 Analysts expect Calgon Carbon Corporation (NYSE:CCC) to report $0.14 EPS on August, 4.They anticipate $0.01 EPS change or 6.67% from last quarter’s $0.15 EPS. CCC’s profit would be $7.19 million giving it 28.66 P/E if the $0.14 EPS is correct. After having $0.10 EPS previously, Calgon Carbon Corporation’s analysts see 40.00% EPS growth. About 42,465 shares traded. Calgon Carbon Corporation (NYSE:CCC) has declined 0.14% since July 26, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 16.84% the S&P500.
Among 5 analysts covering Calgon Carbon (NYSE:CCC), 2 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 3 Hold. Therefore 40% are positive. Calgon Carbon had 6 analyst reports since February 22, 2016 according to SRatingsIntel. The firm has “Hold” rating by Janney Capital given on Thursday, July 13. The firm has “Buy” rating given on Wednesday, May 11 by Janney Capital. The firm has “Outperform” rating given on Tuesday, October 4 by Robert W. Baird. The stock of Calgon Carbon Corporation (NYSE:CCC) has “Neutral” rating given on Monday, February 22 by Roth Capital. Oppenheimer initiated Calgon Carbon Corporation (NYSE:CCC) on Wednesday, June 1 with “Outperform” rating. The stock of Calgon Carbon Corporation (NYSE:CCC) earned “Hold” rating by BB&T Capital on Monday, February 22.
Investors sentiment decreased to 1.16 in 2016 Q4. Its down 0.23, from 1.39 in 2016Q3. It is negative, as 12 investors sold Calgon Carbon Corporation shares while 52 reduced holdings. 23 funds opened positions while 51 raised stakes. 42.63 million shares or 0.20% less from 42.71 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Guggenheim Capital Llc accumulated 0.01% or 177,872 shares. Illinois-based Citadel Advsrs Limited Company has invested 0% in Calgon Carbon Corporation (NYSE:CCC). Barrow Hanley Mewhinney & Strauss Llc, Texas-based fund reported 118,858 shares. Catawba Mgmt Va holds 0.07% of its portfolio in Calgon Carbon Corporation (NYSE:CCC) for 16,780 shares. Panagora Asset Management has 4,355 shares for 0% of their portfolio. Lazard Asset Management Lc, New York-based fund reported 729,919 shares. Keybank Natl Association Oh invested in 52,432 shares or 0.01% of the stock. Cramer Rosenthal Mcglynn Ltd holds 0.19% or 759,096 shares. Tower (Trc) invested 0% in Calgon Carbon Corporation (NYSE:CCC). Mason Street Advisors Limited Liability Company reported 11,064 shares or 0.01% of all its holdings. St Germain D J holds 1.13% or 490,854 shares. Highlander Management Ltd Llc invested in 122,533 shares. Tiaa Cref Investment Mgmt Limited reported 0% in Calgon Carbon Corporation (NYSE:CCC). Pinebridge Limited Partnership holds 0.03% or 50,003 shares. Legal And General Grp Inc Public Limited Company stated it has 0% in Calgon Carbon Corporation (NYSE:CCC).
Since May 30, 2017, it had 0 insider buys, and 1 insider sale for $74,827 activity. Alexander J Rich also sold $74,827 worth of Calgon Carbon Corporation (NYSE:CCC) on Tuesday, May 30.
Calgon Carbon Corporation is a manufacturer of activated carbon, with capabilities in ultraviolet light disinfection. The company has market cap of $824.81 million. The Firm provides purification solutions for drinking water, wastewater, pollution abatement, and a range of industrial and commercial manufacturing processes. It has a 90.57 P/E ratio. The Firm operates through four divisions: Activated Carbon and Service, Equipment, Consumer and Other.
 About 108,221 shares traded. Meritor Inc (MTOR) has risen 104.71% since July 26, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 88.01% the S&P500.
Since January 1, 0001, it had 1 insider purchase, and 8 insider sales for $3.18 million activity. 
